memberdef.name: SDF_DECLARE_VALUE_TYPE_TRAITS

briefdescription.para: An enum that specifies the type of an object.

detaileddescription.para: Objects are entities that have fields and are addressable by path.

briefdescription.para: An enum that identifies the possible specifiers for an SdfPrimSpec.

detaileddescription.para: The SdfSpecifier enum is registered as a TfEnum for converting to and from std::string.

briefdescription.para: An enum that defines permission levels.

detaileddescription.para: Permissions control which layers may refer to or express opinions about a prim. Opinions expressed about a prim, or relationships to that prim, by layers that are not allowed permission to access the prim will be ignored.

listitem.para: SdfPermissionPublic. Public prims can be referred to by anything. (Available to any client.)
SdfPermissionPrivate. Private prims can be referred to only within the local layer stack, and not across references or inherits. (Not available to clients.)

briefdescription.para: An enum that identifies variability types for attributes.

detaileddescription.para: Variability indicates whether the attribute may vary over time and value coordinates, and if its value comes through authoring or or from its owner.

listitem.para: SdfVariabilityVarying. Varying attributes may be directly authored, animated and affected on by Actions. They are the most flexible.
SdfVariabilityUniform. Uniform attributes may be authored only with non-animated values (default values). They cannot be affected by Actions, but they can be connected to other Uniform attributes.

briefdescription.para: An enum for TfError codes related to authoring operations.

listitem.para: SdfAuthoringErrorUnrecognizedFields. This error is raised if SdfLayer::TransferContent, or SdfLayer::SetField API is called for layers of differing schema, and fields from the source layer are not recognized by the target layer's schema.
SdfAuthoringErrorUnrecognizedSpecType. This error is raised in attempts to create specs on layers with spec types that are not recognized by the layer's schema.

A map of variant set names to list of variants in those sets.
A map of source SdfPaths to target SdfPaths for relocation.

Converts from one unit of measure to another.

detaileddescription.para: The fromUnit and toUnit units must be of the same type (for example, both of type SdfLengthUnit).

briefdescription.para: Gets the name for a given /a unit.
Gets a unit for the given /a name.
Given a value, returns if there is a valid corresponding valueType.
Given an sdf valueType name, produce TfType if the type name specifies a valid sdf value type.
Given a value, produce the sdf valueType name.

detaileddescription.para: If you provide a value that does not return true for SdfValueHasValidType, the return value is unspecified.

briefdescription.para: Return role name for typeName.

detaileddescription.para: Return empty token if typeName has no associated role name.

briefdescription.para: Convert dict to a valid metadata dictionary for scene description.

detaileddescription.para: Valid metadata dictionaries have values that are any of SDF_VALUE_TYPES (or VtArrays of those), plus VtDictionary with values of those types (or similarly nested VtDictionaries).
Certain conversions are performed in an attempt to produce a valid metadata dictionary. For example:
Convert std::vector<VtValue> to VtArray<T> where T is the type of the first element in the vector. Fail conversion for empty vectors where a concrete type cannot be inferred.

Convert python sequences to VtArray<T> where T is the type of the first element in the python sequence, when converted to VtValue, if that T is an SDF_VALUE_TYPE). Fail conversion for empty sequences where a concrete type cannot be inferred.
If any values cannot be converted to valid SDF_VALUE_TYPES, omit those elements and add a message to errMsg indicating which values were omitted.
